hands_on_practices.solution:
We seek the total cross section $\sigma=\int_0^\infty2\pi b\,P(b)\,db$, where the probability is given by $P(b)\approx 2p_{LZ}$ for $b<R_c$ and $P(b)=0$ for $b>R_c$.

1. First, find the crossing radius $R_c$. It is defined by the condition $\Delta E(R_c)=0$, where $\Delta E(R) = \hbar\Delta - C_n/R^n$. This gives $\hbar\Delta - C_n/R_c^n = 0$, so:
$$R_c=\Bigl(\frac{C_n}{\hbar\Delta}\Bigr)^{1/n}.$$

2. Next, calculate the rate of change of the energy separation at the crossing. Using the straight-line trajectory $R(t)=\sqrt{b^2+v^2t^2}$, we can find $dR/dt = v^2t/R$. At the crossing time $t_c$, we have $R(t_c)=R_c$, which implies $v|t_c| = \sqrt{R_c^2 - b^2}$.
The time derivative is then:
$$\Bigl|\frac{d\Delta E}{dt}\Bigr|_{t_c}
=\Bigl|-\frac{d}{dt}\frac{C_n}{R^n}\Bigr|_{t_c}
=\Bigl|\frac{nC_n}{R^{n+1}}\frac{dR}{dt}\Bigr|_{t_c}
=\frac{nC_n}{R_c^{n+1}}\frac{v\sqrt{R_c^2-b^2}}{R_c}
=\frac{n\hbar\Delta\,v\sqrt{R_c^2-b^2}}{R_c^2}.$$
In the last step, we used $C_n = \hbar\Delta R_c^n$.

3. Now, we use the Landau–Zener formula for the single-passage probability $p_{LZ}$, with the coupling matrix element $V_{12}=\hbar\Omega_R/2$:
$$p_{LZ}=\frac{2\pi V_{12}^2}{\hbar|d\Delta E/dt|_{t_c}}
=\frac{2\pi (\hbar\Omega_R/2)^2}{\hbar(n\hbar\Delta\,v\sqrt{R_c^2-b^2}/R_c^2)}
=\frac{\pi\hbar^2\Omega_R^2/2}{n\hbar^2\Delta\,v\sqrt{R_c^2-b^2}/R_c^2}
=\frac{\pi\Omega_R^2R_c^2}{2n\Delta\,v\sqrt{R_c^2-b^2}}\,. $$

4. The total cross-section is the integral of the two-passage probability $P(b)=2p_{LZ}$ over all contributing impact parameters:
$$\sigma=\int_0^{R_c} 2\pi b P(b) db = \int_0^{R_c} 2\pi b (2p_{LZ}) db
=\int_0^{R_c} 4\pi b \left( \frac{\pi\Omega_R^2R_c^2}{2n\Delta\,v\sqrt{R_c^2-b^2}} \right) db$$
$$\sigma = \frac{2\pi^2\Omega_R^2R_c^2}{n\Delta\,v}\int_0^{R_c}\frac{b\,db}{\sqrt{R_c^2-b^2}}
=\frac{2\pi^2\Omega_R^2R_c^2}{n\Delta\,v} \left[ -\sqrt{R_c^2-b^2} \right]_0^{R_c} = \frac{2\pi^2\Omega_R^2R_c^3}{n\Delta\,v}\,. $$

5. Finally, we substitute the expression for $R_c$:
$$\sigma
=\frac{2\pi^2\Omega_R^2}{n\,v\,\Delta}
\Bigl(\frac{C_n}{\hbar\Delta}\Bigr)^{3/n}\,. $$
